umask (User File Creation Mask) is used to set the default permissions for newly created files and directories.

When you create a file or directory, Linux assigns default permissions and then subtracts the umask value.

| umask | User Access | Group Access  | Other Access  |
| ----- | ----------- | ------------- | ------------- |
| 0000  | all         | all           | all           |
| 0002  | all         | all           | read, execute |
| 0007  | all         | all           | none          |
| 0022  | all         | read, execute | read, execute |
| 0027  | all         | read, execute | none          |
| 0077  | all         | none          | none          |

